				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-9842883#post-4110679</guid>
				<title>+1</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-9842883/scp-4450#post-4110679</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 06 Jan 2019 16:40:03 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Phiiota</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4300555</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I really like how there are multiple GoI Formats for the same location and I really like the terminal animation as well.</p> <p>Also, a possible error I noticed is that on the Marshall, Carter, and Dark page is that &quot;<em>Marshall</em>&quot; is spelled as &quot;<em>Marshal</em>&quot;:</p> <blockquote> <p style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>RAISA SEARCH METADATA</strong></span></p> <p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>RAISA FILE: Group of Interest</strong></span><br /> <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>GOI-121: <em>Marshal</em>, Carter &amp; Dark</strong></span><br /> <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>FILE CREATED:</strong></span> c. 1925<br /> <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>FILE LAST REVISED BY GOI:</strong></span> March 1938<br /> <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>[TEXT REPRODUCED BELOW]</strong></span></p> </blockquote> <p>I don't know if it's intentional or not. If it's not, I don't want to ruin this by trying to fix it.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
